name: Cheddar and Meowth - a collaboration with my cats
description:
I collaborated with my cats to write a poem composed of word scraps I use in my daily art journaling:

Different?
The establishment has attempted to impose its will on your self-expression.
Men can lay it out unfairly,
trying to convince you there is a standard - 
but there is nothing.
Whatever the reason,
you won't have to nod to it.
Just imagine the rest.

Method:

Collab took place from September 17, 2021 to September 19, 2021 (poem written by me, the human, on September 21, 2021)

Put word scraps in an attractive box lid.
Let the cats discover what's in the attractive box lid.
(they didn't)
Create a summoning circle with cat treats.
Success, words were scattered outside of the box lid onto the floor and tracked around the house on their paws.
Let everything sit for another day.
Added some more cat treats.
Got some more words.
Wrote the poem.
